main event: A sighting of an unidentified, possibly missile-like object traveling at high speed from Pepperell AFB to Thule, Greenland, observed for 7-8 minutes in September 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed visually for a significant duration of 7-8 minutes, indicating a sustained sighting.
The conclusion of the report suggests that the object was possibly a missile, but it remains classified as unidentified.
The sighting was reported by Lt. Daily from Pepperell AFB, Newfoundland.
No photographs or physical evidence were obtained during the observation.
The intelligence officers advised that the sighting was probably not caused by weather or astronomical phenomena.
location: Pepperell AFB, Newfoundland, to Thule, Greenland
